The paper deals with the problem of compressive sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The proposed algorithm is applied to two-dimensional images, hyperspectral images, and videos, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers (ADMM) framework, which is a popular optimization technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of the CACTI and CASSI frameworks further suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
